The paper discusses information security and cryptography, which are core topics in computer security (cs.CR) and information theory (cs.IT). The analysis of different cryptographic algorithms also involves considerations of their implementation and potential vulnerabilities, which are relevant to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the scalability and flexibility of the algorithms, which are topics in distributed systems (cs.DS).
